# Playwright Locator Priority

When writing or updating Playwright tests, locate elements in this order:

1. `page.getByRole()` — preferred default
2. `page.getByLabel()` / `page.getByPlaceholder()` / `page.getByText()`
4. CSS / XPath locators — last resort only

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
await page.locator("#remove-quote").click();

// ✅ GOOD
await page.getByRole("button", { name: "Remove Quote" }).click();
await page.getByRole("button", { name: "Get Quote" }).click();
await page.locator('[data-test="get-quote"]').click();

```

Prefer accessible names and roles so tests mirror how users find the UI.
